content.text: The <ellipse> element is used to create an ellipse.
content.html: The <ellipse> element is used to create an ellipse.

content.text: An ellipse is closely related to a circle. The difference is that an ellipse has an x and a y radius that differs from each other, while a circle has equal x and y radius.
content.html: An ellipse is closely related to a circle. The difference is that an ellipse has an x and a y radius that differs from each other, while a circle has equal x and y radius.

content.text: The <ellipse> element has four basic attributes to position and set the size of the ellipse:
content.html: The <ellipse> element has four basic attributes to position and set the size of the ellipse:

content.code_html:
Attribute Description
rx Required. The x radius of the ellipse
ry Required. The y radius of the ellipse
cx The x-axis center of the ellipse. Default is 0
cy The y-axis center of the ellipse. Default is 0

content.text: The following example creates an ellipse:

content.code:
<svg height="140" width="500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">

<ellipse rx="100" ry="50" cx="120" cy="80"  style="fill:yellow;stroke:green;stroke-width:3" />

</svg>
content.code_html:
<svg height="140" width="500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <ellipse rx="100" ry="50" cx="120" cy="80"
  style="fill:yellow;stroke:green;stroke-width:3" />
</svg>

content.text: The following example creates three ellipses on top of each other:
content.html: The following example creates three ellipses on top of each other:

content.code:
<svg height="150" width="500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">

<ellipse cx="240" cy="100" rx="220" ry="30" fill="purple" />
  
<ellipse cx="220" cy="70" rx="190" ry="20" fill="lime" />
  <ellipse 
cx="210" cy="45" rx="170" ry="15" fill="yellow" />
</svg>
content.code_html:
<svg height="150" width="500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <ellipse cx="240" cy="100" rx="220" ry="30" fill="purple" />
  <ellipse cx="220" cy="70" rx="190" ry="20" fill="lime" />
  <ellipse cx="210" cy="45" rx="170" ry="15" fill="yellow" />
</svg>

content.text: The following example combines two ellipses (one yellow and one white):
content.html: The following example combines two ellipses (one yellow and one white):

content.code:
<svg height="100" width="500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">


<ellipse cx="240" cy="50" rx="220" ry="30"
fill="yellow" />


<ellipse cx="220" cy="50" rx="190" ry="20"
fill="white" />

</svg>
content.code_html:
<svg height="100" width="500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <ellipse cx="240" cy="50" rx="220" ry="30" fill="yellow" />
  <ellipse cx="220" cy="50" rx="190" ry="20" fill="white" />
</svg>
